      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Bad",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Bright Memory Infinite: Gold Edition",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "’s biggest fall from grace is its incredibly short length. My completion time was 2 hours and 36 minutes which is pretty short when comparing it to other shooters in the same elk like Crysis 2 which took me 15 hours to complete. Don't get me wrong, I've loved what I've played, but it makes me wish there was more of it. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Halfway through the game, there's a short stealth section that feels out of place considering how fast-paced the combat is up to that point; it really puts a halt on the flow of the game and it feels like it's been added as padding to extend the run-time. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "At the time of this review, partway through, I came across a Nintendo error code that appeared saying that you have a corrupted memory card. However, after checking my memory SD card, it appeared to be fine, and I don’t seem to be the only player having this issue. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Finally, there is very little to return to once you've completed the campaign apart from playing on different difficulties. Considering this is the gold edition, this seems lacklustre and including some extra modes (like a horde mode or online co-op, for example) would have added some value. But sadly, we’re left wondering what could have been.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
