      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "I like ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Bright Memory Infinite: Gold Edition",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " for its fast and responsive gunplay, sword fighting and for its enemy encounters that make for some really fun fights, I just wish there was more of it. The performance is solid and looks great (if not a little blurry at times) and what is here is enjoyable enough. However, some additional modes would've helped with its longevity. Yet despite this, I've enjoyed my time with the game and for fans of the FPS genre, there is something to enjoy here. Unfortunately though, it's more of a taste-test than a full course meal.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
